Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Neues Testament Heimsuchung der Maria Visitatio" addressed (inside) to "Technische Hochschule Darmstadt z. Hd. V. Herrn Prof. Dr. H. G. Evers 6100 Darmstadt" and dated 30.11.1966

- Extracts from different publications about the 'Visitation' by Rubens
- Correspondence between Olivier Allard and Burchard, Puyvelde, etc. about some photos of Rubens' 'Visitation' (dated 1937)
- Photo of the 'Visitation'  
  
Loose documentation reunited with the folder:   
    
- Photograph of a painting depicting the Exodus (not by Rubens). The annotation on the back mentions monogram "I.H." and date 1693.   
The photograph was mounted on paper by the Rubenianum team. The back side was copied and also mounted on the paper. A note in pencil on the monogram was added by a member of the Rubenianum team.
